<TITLE> 3 state banks get new chairmen </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 9 (bdnews24.com)The government has appointed new chairmen to three state-owned commercial banks, two being Dhaka University professors including the incumbent DUTA president. Finance secretary Mohammad Tarek told bdnews24.com that a notification in this regard was issued from the finance ministry on Wednesday. Khondakar Bazlul Huq, a professor of international relations and president of Dhaka University Teachers Association, has been made chairman of Agrani Bank. Abul Barakat, a professor of Dhaka University economics department, has been appointed chairman of Janata Bank. Former senior official of Sonali Bank, Kazi Baharul Islam, has been appointed chairman of that bank. Bazlul Huq told bdnews24.com that he heard on Wednesday afternoon about the appointment. bdn
